sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K887071
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the first part of our low temperature release system biobrick. It can make e.coli pass the pathway : glucose->pyruvate->2-acetolactate->2,3-Dihydroxy-isovalerate.Plac is the promoter gene.B0034 is the ribosome binding site.zif268 and PBSII are zinc fingers which help enzymes,alsS and ilvC,to bind the specific DNA sequence and work like factorys gathering together to work efficiently.AlsS is the enzyme which is responsible for converting pyruvate into 2-acetolactate.IlvC is responsible for converting 2-acetolactate into 2,3-Dihydroxy-isovalerate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ting Chang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We advance the 2011 igem NCTU_Formosa Team's idea to produce isobutanol more efficiently and successfully.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had been afraid that it is too long to connect all of them become one part of our biobrick.Fortunately,we are successful for connecting all of them with no problems.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539713
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region of AlsS from Bacillus subtilis. It encodes alpha-acetolactate synthase protein which is part of isobutanol biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because of the four RE site, EcoR1, Xba1, Spe1 and Pst1, before and after the coding sequence, those RE site should not exist in coding sequence. There are two Pst1 site, one Xba1 site and one EcoR1 site in original sequence of AlsS. However, those RE site in AlsS has been modified by point mutation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K539711
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region of ilvC from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr(MG1655). It encodes ketol-acid reductoisomerase NAD(P)-binding which is part of the isobutanol biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang, Yi-Pei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because of the four RE site, EcoR1, Xba1, Spe1 and Pst1, before and after the coding gene, we have to delete those RE site in kivd. The RE site in the part has been modified by point mutation.
